      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">April 1,
2009</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Dear
Shareholder:</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>On behalf of our Board of Directors, we
would like to invite you to the Annual General Meeting of Shareholders of Alcon,
Inc. to be held at the Congress Center Metalli, Zug, Switzerland, on Tuesday,
May 5, 2009.&#160;&#160;Various items are proposed for approval at the
meeting.&#160;&#160;The agenda and related information are set out
below.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>Your vote is important.&#160;&#160;If
you are a registered holder, please vote now by proxy so that your shares are
represented at the meeting.&#160;&#160;You can vote your shares by marking your
choices on the enclosed proxy card, and then signing, dat&#173;ing and mailing it
in the enclosed envelope or by following the Internet or telephone voting
instructions on the proxy card.&#160;&#160;Using any of these methods, you
authorize Alcon, Inc. to vote your shares as you specified.&#160;&#160;If you
authorize Alcon, Inc. to vote your shares without giving any instructions, your
shares will be voted in accordance with the proposals of the Board of Directors
with regard to the items listed on the agenda.&#160;&#160;If new proposals
(other than those on the agenda) are being put forth before the meeting, the
Alcon, Inc. representative will vote your shares in accordance with the position
of the Board of Directors.&#160;&#160;Proxy forms must be sent to the Company in
the enclosed envelope, arriving no later than April 28, 2009.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>If you are a registered holder, you may
also authorize the inde&#173;pendent representative, Ms. Andrea Hodel,
Attorney-At-Law, Zug, Swit&#173;zerland, with full rights of substitution, to
vote your shares on your behalf.&#160;&#160;Ms. Hodel&#8217;s address
is:&#160;&#160;Industriestrasse 13c, CH-6304 Zug, Switzerland.&#160;&#160;If you
authorize the independent representative to vote your shares without giving
instructions, your shares will be voted in accordance with the proposals of the
Board of Directors with regard to the items listed on the agenda.&#160;&#160;If
new proposals (other than those on the agenda) are being put forth before the
meeting, the independent representative will abstain from voting your shares
with regards to any such new proposals.&#160;&#160;Proxy forms authorizing the
independent representative to vote your shares on your behalf must be sent to
the Company in the enclosed envelope or directly to the independent
representative, arriving no later than April 28, 2009.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>Alternatively, if you are a registered
holder, you may choose to attend the meet&#173;ing and vote in person, or appoint
a proxy of your choice to vote at the meeting for you.&#160;&#160;The proxy need
not be a shareholder.&#160;&#160;If you choose to attend the meeting in person,
or appoint a proxy to attend on your behalf, your shares can only be voted at
the meeting.&#160;&#160;To select one of these options, please complete the
attendance portion of the enclosed proxy card and return&#160;it&#160;to the
Company in the enclosed envelope, arriving no later than April 28,
2009.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>If you are a beneficial owner, you are
requested to instruct your broker or custodian as to how to vote your shares
using the instruction form provided to you.&#160;&#160;You may also instruct
your broker or custodian to authorize the independent representative to vote
your shares.&#160;&#160;Alternatively, if you wish to vote in person then you
need to:</font></div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">a)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">obtain
      a power of attorney from your broker or other custodian authorizing you to
      vote the shares held for you by that broker or custodian, and request an
      admission card using the power of attorney;
or</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">b)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">become
      a registered holder no later than April 15, 2009, and request an admission
      card by that date.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>Each holder wishing to attend the
meeting in person must present his/her admission card before 1:45 p.m. on May 5,
2009, at one of the control offices at the meeting location for
validation.&#160;&#160;Doors open at 1:00 p.m.&#160;&#160;<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Registered shareholders who have
appointed Alcon, Inc. or the independent representative as a proxy and
beneficial owners who have not obtained a power of attorney from their broker or
custodian may not attend the meeting in person or send an alternate proxy of
their choice to represent them at the meeting.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>Please note that shareholders who have
sold their shares before the meeting date are not entitled to vote or
participate in the meeting.</font></div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Under
Swiss statutory law, the Board of Directors may seek discharge from the
shareholders upon approval by the shareholders of the annual financial
statements.&#160;&#160;If discharge is granted, the corporation and those
shareholders who have voted in favor of discharge cannot assert any claims based
on Swiss corporation law for directors&#8217; liability with respect to matters then
known to the shareholders.&#160;&#160;The right to assert liability claims still
exists, however, with respect to matters not known to the shareholders on the
date on which discharge was granted.</font></div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 21.6pt"></font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Kevin Buehler. </font>Mr. Buehler
was appointed President and Chief Executive Officer of Alcon, Inc. effective
April 1, 2009.&#160;&#160;Mr. Buehler joined Alcon in 1984.&#160;&#160;In 1996,
after holding a series of sales management positions with increasing
responsibility in the Consumer Products Division, Mr. Buehler expanded his
experience into the pharmaceutical and surgical business areas, leading the
Company's U.S. Managed Care and Falcon Generic Pharmaceutical
groups.&#160;&#160;In 1998 he was promoted to a Vice President position and in
1999, he led the U.S. Consumer Products Division as Vice President and General
Manager. From 2002 to 2004, Mr. Buehler was International Area Vice President
with responsibility for the Company's operations in Latin America, Canada,
Australia and the Far East.&#160;&#160;From 2004 to 2006, he was Senior Vice
President, Alcon United States.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;He served as Senior Vice
President, Alcon United States and Chief Marketing Officer from February 2006
through December 2006.&#160;&#160;He served as Senior Vice President, Global
Markets and Chief Marketing Officer of Alcon Laboratories, Inc. from January
2007 through March 2009.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 18pt"></font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Paul Bulcke. </font>Paul Bulcke
joined the Alcon, Inc. Board in May 2008.&#160;&#160;He has served as Chief
Executive Officer of Nestl&#233; S.A. since April 2008.<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">&#160;</font>Mr. Bulcke began his
career in 1977 as a financial analyst for Scott Graphics International in
Belgium before moving to the Nestl&#233; group in 1979 as a marketing
trainee.&#160;&#160;From 1980 to 1996 he held various marketing, sales and
division functions in Nestl&#233; Peru, Nestl&#233; Ecuador and Nestl&#233; Chile before moving
back to Europe as Managing Director of Nestl&#233; Portugal.&#160;&#160;Between 1998
and 2003 he was Managing Director of Nestl&#233; Czech and Slovak Republic, and then
Nestl&#233; Germany.&#160;&#160;In 2004, he was appointed as Executive Vice
President, responsible for Zone Americas.&#160;&#160;Mr. Bulcke serves as a
director of Nestl&#233; S.A. and Co-Chairman of the Supervisory Board of Cereal
Partners Worldwide.&#160;&#160;Mr. Bulcke graduated from the University of
Leuven as a Commercial Engineer and obtained his post graduate in Management at
the University of Gent in Belgium.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Joan W. Miller,
M.D.&#160;&#160;</font>Joan W. Miller is proposed to be elected to the board of
directors as a replacement for Gerhard Mayr.&#160;&#160;The term of office of
Gerhard N. Mayr expires at the Annual General Meeting </font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
          </div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">
          </div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">to be
held on May 5, 2009.&#160;&#160;Mr. Mayr will retire from office and will not
stand for re-election.&#160;&#160;Dr. Miller is proposed to be elected to the
board of directors for a three-year term of office.</font></div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Dr.
Miller is Chief and Chair of Ophthalmology and Henry Willard Williams Professor
of Ophthalmology at the Massachusetts Eye and Ear Infirmary and Harvard Medical
School.&#160;&#160;Dr. Miller&#8217;s research interests are focused on ocular
neovascularization, particularly as it relates to macular degeneration and
diabetic retinopathy, including the role of growth factors, the development of
antiangiogenic therapy, and photodynamic therapy.&#160;&#160;Dr. Miller has
received numerous awards, including the Rosenthal Award of the Macula Society,
the Retina Research Award from the Club Jules Gonin and the Alcon Research
Institute Award.&#160;&#160;Dr. Miller&#8217;s professional affiliations include
American Academy of Ophthalmology, Association for Research in Vision and
Ophthalmology, Inc. (ARVO), and the New England Ophthalmological Society
(NEOS).</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Hermann Wirz.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-STYLE: italic">&#160;</font>Hermann
Wirz is proposed to be elected to the board of directors as a replacement for
Paul Polman who resigned from Alcon&#8217;s board of directors effective September 6,
2008.&#160;&#160;Mr. Polman was a member of the class of directors whose term of
office would expire in 2011.&#160;&#160;Mr. Wirz is proposed to be elected to
the board of directors for a two-year term of office.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Mr. Wirz
began his career in 1968 in financial and management accounting for Electrical
Company Lucerne Switzerland.&#160;&#160;From 1969 through 1971, he held a
management accounting position for Shell Switzerland.&#160;&#160;He joined
Nestl&#233; in 1972 and worked in industrial accounting and budgeting functions for
Nestl&#233; England, Spain and Venezuela.&#160;&#160;He subsequently was appointed
Manager Operational Control Latin America for Nestec Switzerland in 1980 and in
1984 was promoted to Director of Finance &amp; Control for Nestl&#233; Peru, and for
Nestl&#233; Venezuela in 1989.&#160;&#160;Mr. Wirz was appointed Executive Vice
President and Chief Financial Officer of Nestl&#233; Mexico in 1995 and served in
that position through 2000.&#160;&#160;In 2001, he was appointed Chief
Accounting Officer (Senior Vice President as Head of Group Accounting &amp;
Reporting) for Nestl&#233; S.A., Switzerland.&#160;&#160;He was a member of the Swiss
Chamber of Commerce in Peru, Venezuela and Mexico and also a member of the
Admission Board of the Swiss Stock Exchange.&#160;&#160;He achieved his degree
in Business Administration from Lucerne, Switzerland, and has completed the
Programme for Executive Development at the International Institute for
Management Development (IMD) in Lausanne, Switzerland.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 15.95pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 16pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Item
7</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 15.95pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Approval
of Share Cancellation</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top" style="LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt;">
              <td style="WIDTH: 18pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;
      <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">A.&#160;</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Proposal</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">The Board
of Directors proposes that 1,043,400 shares, at CHF 0.20 par value per share,
which have been repurchased by Alcon, Inc. be cancelled and that, as a result,
the share capital of Alcon, Inc. be reduced from 60,944,541.20 to CHF
60,735,861.20.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Article 4
para. 1 of the Alcon, Inc. Articles of Association shall be amended
accordingly.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top" style="LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt;">
              <td style="WIDTH: 18pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;
      <font style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold">B</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">.&#160;</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Explanations</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">The Board
of Directors has authorized the repurchase of shares of the Company from time to
time. The repurchased shares may be held in treasury and reused at a later date
or, alternatively, may be cancelled.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">The Board
of Directors now proposes that the Annual General Meeting approve the
cancellation of 1,043,400 repurchased shares and that the share capital in
Article 4 para. 1 of the Alcon, Inc. Articles of Association be reduced
accordingly.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">KPMG AG
as statutory auditors have confirmed in a special audit report prepared for the
Annual General Meeting that, as of March 31, 2009, the claims of creditors would
be covered even with the proposed reduction in capital.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>

8</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 15.95pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Editorial

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>

of Directors proposes to amend articles 9, 17 lit. b), 18 lit. j), 27 para. 1
and 3 as well as heading C) of the Articles of Association as follows (proposed
changes are marked):</font></div>

      9 Ordentliche Generalversammlungen</font></div>
              </td>
              <td valign="top" width="4%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></td>
              <td valign="top" width="36%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Article
      9 Ordinary Shareholders' Meetings</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>

              <td valign="top" width="36%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;

            <tr>
              <td valign="top" width="36%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Die
      ordentliche Generalversammlung findet allj&#228;hrlich innerhalb von sechs
      Monaten nach Schluss des Gesch&#228;ftsjahres statt; sp&#228;testens zwanzig Tage
      vor der Versammlung sind der Gesch&#228;ftsbericht und der Revisionsbericht
      <font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: line-through">mit dem
      Bericht der Konzernpr&#252;fer</font> den Aktion&#228;ren am Gesellschaftssitz zur
      Einsicht aufzulegen. Jeder Aktion&#228;r kann verlangen, dass ihm unverz&#252;glich
      eine Ausfertigung dieser Unterlagen ohne Kostenfolge zugestellt wird. Die
      im Aktienbuch eingetragenen Aktion&#228;re werden hier&#252;ber durch schriftliche
      Mitteilung unterrichtet.</font></div>
              </td>
              <td valign="top" width="4%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></td>
              <td valign="top" width="36%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      Ordinary Shareholders' Meeting shall be held each year within six months
      after the close of the fiscal year of the Company; the business report and
      the Auditor's report<font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: line-through">, together with the
      group auditor's report,</font> shall be made available for inspection by
      the shareholders at the place of incorporation of the Company no later
      than twenty days prior to the meeting. Each shareholder is entitled to
      request immediate delivery of a copy of these documents free of charge.
      Shareholders of record will be notified of this in
  writing.</font></div>
              </td>

                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 18pt; TEXT-INDENT: -18pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">j)die
      Aufl&#246;sung der Gesellschaft<font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: line-through"> ohne
      Liquidation</font>;</font></div>

      </font>Der Revisionsstelle<font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: line-through"> und dem

              <td style="WIDTH: 18pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;
      <font style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold">B</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">.</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Explanations</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Since
January 1, 2008, the Swiss Code of Obligations requires a qualified majority for
decisions on any kind of dissolution of a Swiss
corporation.&#160;&#160;Accordingly, the Board of Directors proposes to adopt
Article 18 lit. j of the Articles of Association.&#160;&#160;Article 727 <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">et seq</font>. of the Swiss Code of
Obligations do no longer provide for the designation "group auditors" (<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Konzernpr&#252;fer</font>), but refer to
"auditors" (<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Revisionsstelle</font>) for auditors
who audit the statutory financial statements as well as the consolidated
financial statements.&#160;&#160;Accordingly, the Board of Directors proposes to
delete the reference to "Group Auditors" (<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Konzernpr&#252;fer</font>) in the
Articles of Association.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 15.95pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 16pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Organizational
Matters</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Admission
cards/Voting material</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font>Shareholders who are registered in
the share register on <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">March 19,
2009</font>, will receive the proxy and admission form (including the voting
material) directly from the share registrar of the
Company.&#160;&#160;Beneficial owners of shares will receive an instruction form
from their broker or custodian to indicate how they wish their shares to be
voted.&#160;&#160;Beneficial owners who wish to attend the shareholders&#8217; meeting
in person are requested to obtain a power of attorney from their broker or other
custodian that authorizes them to vote the shares held for them by the broker or
custodian, and to request an admission card using the power of
attorney.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font>Beneficial owners of shares and
shareholders registered in the share register as of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">March 19, 2009</font>, are
enti&#173;tled to vote and may participate in the shareholders<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#8217;</font> meet&#173;ing unless they sell
their shares before the shareholders<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#8217;</font> meeting takes
place.&#160;&#160;Each share carries one vote.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font>Persons who have <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">acquired </font>shares after March
19, 2009, but on or before <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">April 15, 2009, </font>will receive
the proxy and admission form (including the voting material) shortly before the
meeting.&#160;&#160;Shareholders who have acquired shares after that date may
not attend the Annual General Meeting of Alcon, Inc.&#160;&#160;Shareholders who
have <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">sold </font>their shares
before the meeting date are not entitled to vote or participate in the
meeting.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Granting
of powers of attorney</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font>Registered shareholders who are
unable to participate in the shareholders<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#8217;</font> meeting may appoint as a
representative another shareholder, a third party, their bank or a corporate
proxy holder.&#160;&#160;Ms. Andrea Hodel, Attorney-at-Law, Industriestrasse
13c, CH-6304 Zug, Switzerland,<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font>is also avail&#173;able as
an independent representative, with full rights of substitution, in the sense of
article 689c of the Swiss Code of Ob&#173;ligations.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 12.55pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">The power of attorney on the
application form must be filled in accordingly, signed and returned to the
address indicated below or to the independent representative arriving no later
than April 28, 2009.&#160;&#160;Powers of attorney are revocable, but Alcon,
Inc. will treat any power of attorney as being valid unless the revocation has
been sent in writing to Alcon, Inc. at the address referred to
below.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt"></font>Alcon, Inc.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt"></font>c/o BNY Mellon Shareowner
Services</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt"></font>P.O. Box 3531</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt"></font>S.
Hackensack,&#160;&#160;NJ&#160;&#160;07606-9231</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font>Registered shareholders who have
appointed Alcon, Inc. or the independent representative as a proxy may not
attend the meeting in person or send a proxy of their choice to the
meeting.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font>With regard to the items listed on
the agenda and without any explicit instructions to the contrary, the corporate
proxy holder and independent representative will vote according to the proposals
of the Board of Directors.&#160;&#160;If new proposals (other than those on the
agenda) are being put forth before the meeting, the corporate proxy holder will
vote in accordance with the position of the Board of Directors and the
independent representative will abstain from voting regarding new
proposals.&#160;&#160;Shareholders who sign and return their power of attorney
without indi&#173;cating a representative will be represented by the corporate
proxy holder.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

Beneficial owners who have not obtained a power of attorney from their broker or

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font>Proxy holders of deposited shares in

to inform the Company of the number of the shares they rep&#173;resent as soon as
possible, but no later than May 5, 2009, 1:00 p.m. at the admis&#173;sion
office.</font></div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 28.35pt"></font>The admission office opens on the

    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Alcon
Laboratories, Inc. Announces Promotion</font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Effective
April 1, Bill Barton was promoted to Senior Vice President, International
Markets of Alcon Laboratories, Inc. with direct responsibility for all markets
outside the United States.&#160;&#160;He will also chair the Global Marketing
Committee, which is responsible for coordinating product development profiles,
pricing and promotion strategies globally.</font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Barton
joined Alcon in 1989 when the company acquired CooperVision Surgical, where he
had worked since 1985.&#160;&#160;Since then he has held positions of increasing
responsibility and global diversity in sales, marketing and general management,
including the role of Vice President and Area President of Alcon&#8217;s operations in
Canada, Australia and the Far East.&#160;&#160;Most recently, he served as Vice
President, Global Marketing and Area President, U.S.</font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div><br></body>
